The paper discusses the use of user-centered methods to design programming languages, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). The paper also specifically mentions the design of two programming languages, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the usability of the languages, which could fall under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) and software development (cs.SD).
